<br>
BUT ... if going from 155 STR to 255 STR shows a 3 to 5 percent increase in DPS ... and you can get your str to 255 with some buffs, then, yeah, even though it's MINISCULE, it's still more DPS than you had before.<br>
<br>
I dunno, I guess I just see people dismiss raising stats all the time on the boards ... and then turn around and post something in an equipment thread asking about which gear between item1 and item2 is better and it's almost invariably between two items that only have minimal stat differences.<br>
<br>
It gets kind of silly after awhile.<br>
<br>
Like, I have a monk friend who's constantly asking me which weapon in his bag to mainhand, which to offhand. I finally just got fed up after 40 levels of this advice, and told him to use the ones he likes best. And he's a MONK ... they don't have that many weapons choices. If this guy were to play a warrior ... I'd go INSANE.<br>
<br>
-Wubao <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=haass>Haass</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>will kick your @$$</span><br>  Posts: 910<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/16/03 11:18 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: ...</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>BUT ... if going from 155 STR to 255 STR shows a 3 to 5 percent increase in DPS ... and you can get your str to 255 with some buffs, then, yeah, even though it's MINISCULE, it's still more DPS than you had before.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I agree, but that's a buff situation, and thankfully, with the Focus line being the way it is, the only stat that doesn't end up getting buffed on a raid directly by a shaman is Agility..and I'd guess about 50% or so of shammies will toss down an AGI talisman, and you can do what you want with it.<br>
<br>
So it's obvious everyone is gonna get the 67 str and 50 dex or whatever from Focus anyway, the real question is &quot;is it worth going for stats on your gear?&quot; and the answer to that is no.  For you to add 100 points of strength to your current gear setup, for <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>most</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> people, you'd have to take some pretty hefty cuts in other places to manage it.<br>
<br>
i'm over 200 str with a Focus anyway..I ain't gonna sweat the last 50 points.  I'm sure it would be another couple of percent DPS, but for what it would take me to add 50 str on to my gear, i'd be losing a crapload of AC/Hp, and that is the crux of the argument. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showMessageRange?topicID=3161.topic&start=1&stop=20>1</a> <b>2</b>  </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showPrevMessage?topicID=3161.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showNextMessage?topicID=3161.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.emailToFriend?topicID=3161.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.threadControl?topicID=3161.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=3161.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to receive email notification of replies"> Click to receive email notification of replies</a> <br>  <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=3161.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/unsubscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to stop receiving email notification of replies"> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies</a> <br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><t